{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "4 · WBR: Weekly Callouts",
  "description": "Full WBR callout pipeline: ingest dashboard → gather context → analyst → writer → blind review → correction loop → report. All 10 markets with special depth on AU and MX.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the full WBR callout pipeline. This is a multi-phase process. Execute each phase completely before moving to the next.\n\nIMPORTANT: Determine the current ISO week number from today's date. Use that as W{NN} throughout. The previous week is W{NN-1}.\n\n=== PHASE 0: DASHBOARD INGESTION ===\nThis step is MANDATORY. Do not skip it.\n\n1. Find the most recent WW Dashboard xlsx file. Check ~/shared/context/intake/ for files matching 'AB SEM WW Dashboard_Y26 W{NN}.xlsx' or similar.\n2. Run the ingester: python3 ~/shared/tools/dashboard-ingester/ingest.py <path_to_xlsx>\n3. If openpyxl is not installed, run: pip install openpyxl\n4. If the ingester fails, debug and fix the issue before proceeding. Common issues:\n   - spend_op2 KeyError: use .get() for budget dict access\n   - ie%CCP reading CPA instead of IECCP: ensure _read_ieccp scans from the IECCP header row (row 15), not from row 1\n5. Verify output: data briefs for all 10 markets, WW summary, JSON extract.\n6. Spot-check ie%CCP values in the data briefs. If any market shows ie%CCP > 200%, the ingester is reading CPA values instead of ie%CCP ratios. Fix the _read_ieccp method.\n\n=== PHASE 0.5: CONTEXT LOAD ===\nRead these files to establish baseline context (order matters):\n1. ~/shared/context/body/body.md\n2. ~/shared/context/body/spine.md\n3. ~/shared/context/body/eyes.md (market health, competitive landscape)\n4. ~/shared/context/body/hands.md (recent actions, what's been done)\n5. ~/shared/context/active/current.md (live state)\n6. ~/shared/context/active/callouts/callout-principles.md (includes ie%CCP reference, pipeline rules, confidence threshold)\n7. ~/.kiro/steering/richard-writing-style.md (core writing voice)\n8. ~/.kiro/steering/richard-style-wbr.md (WBR-specific writing style)\n9. ~/.kiro/steering/richard-style-amazon.md (Amazon writing conventions)\n10. shared/context/active/callouts/ww/ww-summary-2026-w{NN}.md (just generated by ingester)\n11. shared/context/active/callouts/ww/projections-ww.md (WW projections tracker)\n\n=== PHASE 1: BROAD CONTEXT GATHERING ===\nScan these sources for anything relevant to this week's paid search performance across all markets. Take notes on what you find — this context feeds the analysts.\n\n1. EMAILS: Search recent emails (last 7 days) for keywords: \"WBR\", \"callout\", \"paid search\", \"registrations\", \"CPA\", \"dashboard\", \"weekly\", \"performance\". Note any performance discussions, escalations, or context shared by teammates.\n\n2. MEETINGS/HEDY: Read ~/shared/context/meetings/README.md to find relevant meeting series files. Check for any meetings in the last 7 days that discussed paid search performance, WBR prep, market updates, or competitive dynamics. Read the relevant meeting notes files.\n\n3. TASKS: Check Microsoft To-Do lists for any callout-related or WBR-related tasks. Check ~/shared/context/active/rw-tracker.md for active callout work.\n\n4. CHANGE HISTORY: For each market, read the change log at shared/context/active/callouts/{market}/{market}-change-log.md. These track bid strategy changes, negative keyword work, URL migrations, promo changes, and other actions that affect performance. STALENESS CHECK: If the most recent entry in a change log is older than the target week, the log is stale. Do NOT claim 'no changes were made' — the log just hasn't been updated. Omit action framing from the callout and flag in the Note.\n\n5. DASHBOARD DATA: Read the data briefs for all 10 markets at shared/context/active/callouts/{market}/{market}-data-brief-2026-w{NN}.md (generated in Phase 0).\n\n6. MARKET CONTEXT: Read all 10 market context files at shared/context/active/callouts/{market}/{market}-context.md.\n\n7. PREVIOUS CALLOUTS: Read last week's callouts for all 10 markets at shared/context/active/callouts/{market}/{market}-2026-w{NN-1}.md for continuity.\n\n8. PREVIOUS REVIEWS: Read last week's review at shared/context/active/callouts/ww/ww-review-2026-w{NN-1}.md if it exists, to understand quality trends and recurring issues.\n\nSPECIAL FOCUS — AU and MX:\nFor these two markets, go deeper:\n- Read the previous 2 weeks of callouts (not just 1) for trend continuity\n- Read the previous analysis briefs for narrative thread tracking\n- Read the projections file at shared/context/active/callouts/{market}/{market}-projections.md for projection accuracy tracking\n- Search emails specifically for 'Australia', 'AU', 'Mexico', 'MX', 'Lena', 'Alexis', 'Lorena' for market-specific context\n- Check for any Hedy meeting notes mentioning these markets specifically\n\nCompile a context summary noting: key themes this week, market-specific signals, actions taken, competitive changes, and anything unusual. This summary is your working memory for the analyst phase.\n\n=== PHASE 2: ANALYSIS (10 runs — one market-analyst invocation per market) ===\nInvoke the market-analyst agent as a sub-agent, once per market. Pass the market code, week number, and your context summary.\n\nIMPORTANT: Run these sequentially so each can reference cross-market patterns. The market-analyst reads {market}-context.md for market-specific rules, queries prior observations for learned experience, and writes agent state after each run.\n\nFor each market in order [AU, MX, US, CA, JP, UK, DE, FR, IT, ES]:\n  1. Invoke market-analyst with market={market}, week=W{NN}\n  2. Verify {market}-analysis-2026-w{NN}.md exists before proceeding to the next market\n\nEach produces: analysis brief + projection update + agent state records. Verify all 10 analysis briefs exist before proceeding to Phase 3.\n\n=== PHASE 3: WRITING (10 runs — one callout-writer invocation per market) ===\nInvoke the callout-writer agent as a sub-agent, once per market. They consume the analysis briefs from Phase 2.\n\nCRITICAL WRITER RULES (from W13 learnings):\n- Prose (above ---): ONLY claims verifiable from the data brief. Metric changes, percentages, trends.\n- Note section: Internal PS context. Campaign changes, migrations, competitors, stakeholder actions.\n- This separation is what the confidence score measures. Target: >66% confidence.\n- Include CPA WoW% in every headline for consistency.\n- Compute WoW% from underlying numbers, not rounded display values.\n- If analyst-adjusted projection differs >10% from ingester estimate, label it in the Note.\n\nFor each market in order [AU, MX, US, CA, JP, UK, DE, FR, IT, ES]:\n  1. Invoke callout-writer with market={market}, week=W{NN}\n  2. Verify {market}-2026-w{NN}.md exists before proceeding to the next market\n\nThe callout-writer reads {market}-context.md for market-specific writing rules (has_yoy, has_ieccp, headline_extras, regional_summary) and logs agent state after each run.\n\nVerify all 10 callout drafts exist.\n\n=== PHASE 4: BLIND REVIEW ===\nInvoke the callout-reviewer agent as a BLIND review.\n\nBLIND REVIEW RULES:\n- The reviewer gets ONLY: callout drafts + raw data briefs + callout principles.\n- It does NOT get: analysis briefs, context files, meeting notes, change logs.\n- It must independently verify every claim against the data brief numbers.\n- It scores each market on 6 dimensions (1-10): Data Accuracy, Attribution Quality, Narrative Quality, Style Compliance, Cross-Market Coherence, Confidence Score (%).\n- Confidence Score: what % of the narrative is verifiable from the data brief alone. Claims requiring external context (migrations, competitors, budget changes, regulatory events) reduce confidence.\n- For each market, list specific 'context gaps' — claims the writer made that the data brief doesn't support.\n\nOutput: shared/context/active/callouts/ww/ww-review-2026-w{NN}.md\n\n=== PHASE 4.5: CORRECTION LOOP ===\nApply the 66% confidence threshold.\n\n1. Any market with Confidence < 66% gets sent back to its writer agent with:\n   - The reviewer's specific feedback\n   - The relevant coand MX highlights (since these are hands-on markets)\n- Suggested next steps (e.g., 'review AU callout — reviewer flagged headline format')\n- Note any ingester bugs found and fixed during this run"
  }
}
